1. Make sure XAMPP is correctly installed on your computer.

2. clone the repository to your computer.

3. Open XAMPP and start Apache and MySQL.

4. Open your browser and go to localhost/phpmyadmin and create a new user 'adam' with password 'Qq2834262' and give it all privileges.

5. Create a database 'blog', and upload the SQL dump (blog-tables.sql) to the database.
